<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>When working with file uploads in Zend_Form you have to call receive on every file element.</p>

<p>For simplicity it would be nice when we have a receive() method in Zend_Form which would proxy to the file elements receive() method.</p>

<p>So instead of</p>

<pre class="highlight"><code>
if (!$form-&gt;file1-&gt;receive()) { 
    print_r($form-&gt;file1-&gt;getMessages());
    exit; 
}  
if (!$form-&gt;file2-&gt;receive()) { 
    print_r($form-&gt;file2-&gt;getMessages());
    exit; 
}  
</code></pre>

<p>a simple</p>

<pre class="highlight"><code>
if (!$form-&gt;receive()) { 
    print_r($form-&gt;getMessages());
    exit; 
}  
</code></pre>

<p>would be enough.
Especially usefull when working with much file upload elements.</p>

